  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In a clinical trial of 19 patients, 44 single-rooted teeth will be randomly assigned to one
      of four groups for: 1) no treatment, 2) manual root planing with curettes; 3) root planing
      with piezoelectric ultrasonic scraper [PU]; or 4) root planing with vertically oscillating
      ultrasonic device [VOU]. Post-treatment, the teeth will be extracted and their topography
      analyzed in 124 observations with white light confocal microscopy, measuring the roughness
      parameters Rp, Rv, Rt, Ra, Rq, Rku, and Rsk.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
